main event: A large, pulsing, steaming mass of unknown material descended from the east and was observed by at least 25 persons in Davidsonville, Maryland on February 3, 1955.
interesting points: The object was described as being large and made of unknown material, The sighting lasted for several hours, AFOSI required several minutes to clear railroad rolling equipment, Over 25 witnesses observed the incident, The object's trajectory was all to earth.
sighted object: a large, pulsing, steaming mass of unknown material
